claim.claim-text:
1. A method of presenting a plurality of auditory communications having associated data including information about at least one auditory term identified in the communications, comprising:
using a processor to select each of the plurality of auditory communications based on the associated data;
providing via a display at least one visual representation of the auditory term;
providing via the display a plurality of links each associated with an occurrence of the auditory term in a corresponding portion of the auditory content of one of the plurality of communications;
providing a visual representation of at least one policy invoked by at least one auditory term identified or not identified in one of the plurality of communications, wherein the visual representation includes at least one policy violated by an auditory communication of the plurality of auditory communications, and wherein the at least one invoked policy comprises data regarding Sarbanes-Oxley, HIPAA, SEC, NASD, or corporate regulations;
determining an action to perform based on the at least one invoked policy; and
when a link is selected, playing via an audio output device the corresponding portion of the auditory content of one of the plurality of communications that corresponds to the selected link, wherein the corresponding portion includes the occurrence of the auditory term and at least a portion of the communication following the occurrence of the auditory term.

14. A system for presenting a plurality of auditory communications having associated data including information about at least one auditory term identified in the communications, comprising:
a computer configured to execute via program instructions from memory, the program instructions comprising:
select each of the plurality of auditory communications based on the associated data;
provide at least one visual representation of the auditory term;
provide a plurality of links each associated with an occurrence of the auditory term in a corresponding portion of the auditory content of one of the plurality of communications; and
provide a visual representation of at least one policy invoked by at least one auditory term identified or not identified in one of the plurality of communications, wherein the visual representation includes at least one policy violated by an auditory communication of the plurality of auditory communications, and wherein the at least one invoked policy comprises data regarding Sarbanes-Oxley, HIPAA, SEC, NASD, or corporate regulations;
determine an action to perform based on the at least one invoked policy; and
when a link is selected, play the corresponding portion of the auditory content of one of the plurality of communications that corresponds to the selected link, wherein the corresponding portion includes the occurrence of the auditory term and at least a portion of the communication following the occurrence of the auditory term.

19. A computer program product for presenting a plurality of auditory communications having associated data representing at least one auditory term identified in the communications, comprising a non-transitory computer usable medium having machine readable code embodied therein, comprising:
selecting each of the plurality of auditory communications based on the associated data;
providing at least one visual representation of the auditory term;
providing a plurality of links each associated with an occurrence of the auditory term in a corresponding portion of the auditory content of one of the plurality of communications;
providing a visual representation of at least one policy invoked by at least one auditory term identified or not identified in one of the plurality of communications, wherein the visual representation includes at least one policy violated by an auditory communication of the plurality of auditory communications, and wherein the at least one invoked policy comprises data regarding Sarbanes-Oxley, HIPAA, SEC, NASD, or corporate regulations;
determining an action to perform based on the at least one invoked policy; and
when a link is selected, playing the corresponding portion of the auditory content of one of the plurality of communications that corresponds to the selected link, wherein the corresponding portion includes the occurrence of the auditory term and at least a portion of the communication following the occurrence of the auditory term.
